title: Bug 4121: JarExporter causes out of sync
description: When exporting a directory (project) and placing the exported jar in the same directory, an out of sync message is displayed when overwriting the exported jar file for the second time.
OB: When exporting a directory (project) and placing the exported jar in the same directory, an out of sync message is displayed when overwriting the exported jar file for the second time.
EB: The exported jar should be successfully overwritten without triggering an out of sync message.
SR:
1. Export a directory (project).
2. Place the exported jar in the same directory.
3. Overwrite the exported jar file for the second time.
